abstract: Jia Tolentino’s essay collection, a highly anticipated new novel from Téa Obreht, a Japanese thriller and more.
snippet: Jia Tolentino’s essay collection, a highly anticipated new novel from Téa Obreht, a Japanese thriller and more.
lead_paragraph: This month brings some notable debuts, including the novels “The Dearly Beloved” and “A Particular Kind of Black Man,” and Sarah M. Broom’s memoir of New Orleans, “The Yellow House.” Olga Tokarczuk, the winner of last year’s Man Booker International Prize, returns with a new twist on a murder mystery, and literary criticism from Jess Row connects storytelling and gentrification.

abstract: Lower-polling candidates had their moments, but none outshone the front-runners, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren.
snippet: Lower-polling candidates had their moments, but none outshone the front-runners, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren.
lead_paragraph: Those hoping for an underdog candidate to run away with Tuesday night’s debate did not get their wish. The winners — at least in the initial assessment — were the night’s two front-runners, Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren.

abstract: In an extended interview, the California senator explains why she thinks litmus-test questions aren’t helpful and how she is approaching this campaign.
snippet: In an extended interview, the California senator explains why she thinks litmus-test questions aren’t helpful and how she is approaching this campaign.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris has emerged as one of the most important candidates in the Democratic primary, besting Joseph R. Biden Jr. in a debate last month and exciting liberal voters who see her as a strong challenger to President Trump. But Ms. Harris has eluded ideological definition for much of the race.

abstract: Invoking family stories of coming to America, many left-leaning voters in the multiethnic city of Racine say immigrants should enter legally.
snippet: Invoking family stories of coming to America, many left-leaning voters in the multiethnic city of Racine say immigrants should enter legally.
lead_paragraph: RACINE, Wis. — In this old manufacturing city that supported Hillary Clinton in 2016, dislike for President Trump runs wide and deep. Images of crying children at the Mexican border typically serve as Exhibit A on the list of grievances that Democratic voters cite against the president.

abstract: Elvis’s bona fides were in question when he returned to the stage after more than eight years. His ’69 comeback show was a make-or-break gamble.
snippet: Elvis’s bona fides were in question when he returned to the stage after more than eight years. His ’69 comeback show was a make-or-break gamble.
lead_paragraph: The 1960s may have been a wildly transformative decade in the history of popular music, but for Elvis Presley it was something of a black hole.

abstract: Modern Love in miniature, featuring reader-submitted stories of no more than 100 words.
snippet: Modern Love in miniature, featuring reader-submitted stories of no more than 100 words.
lead_paragraph: My twin brother has autism and can’t talk much. I’m a writer. Mother says I sucked out all the words from him in the womb. When we were 12, I walked into my brother’s room and simply said, “I’m gay.” I had never said those words out loud before. I figured he couldn’t tell anyone even if he wanted to. He looked at me, his expression unchanged. I started to cry. My twin didn’t understand what I had told him, or what being gay meant, but he saw that I was sad and reached out for my hand. — Sarah Emily Baum

headline_main: Tiny Love Stories: ‘We’re Not Dating, but We’re Still Sleeping Together’

abstract: As Democrats gather for the next presidential debates this week, several are struggling with fund-raising. An accounting maneuver last month made some appear to have more cash on hand than they did.
snippet: As Democrats gather for the next presidential debates this week, several are struggling with fund-raising. An accounting maneuver last month made some appear to have more cash on hand than they did.
lead_paragraph: Staff members for a half dozen Democratic presidential candidates did not receive their final June paycheck that month. Instead, their campaigns nudged payday into July, an accounting maneuver that obscured payroll costs and temporarily made it look like candidates had more cash on hand than they actually did.

abstract: Years after her death, the writer Doreen Gamboa Fernandez is gaining a following among Filipino-American chefs for the way she explored the cuisine from the bottom up.
snippet: Years after her death, the writer Doreen Gamboa Fernandez is gaining a following among Filipino-American chefs for the way she explored the cuisine from the bottom up.
lead_paragraph: When their safe houses in Manila were no longer safe, the rebels took shelter at the airy bungalow of Doreen Gamboa Fernandez, a sugar planter’s daughter turned literature professor and food writer.
